               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1338" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1338" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1338" type="surname" value="HOW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1338" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD HOW.</persName>
                  </hi> I am master of the <hi rend="italic">Arab</hi>—it is lying at Mill-hole, on the Thames—I left the articles stated and my money safe in my bed-case in my state-room, on 12th Nov.—I missed them on Sunday morning the 14th, bet<lb></lb>ween five and six o'clock—the prisoner was my apprentice—he deserted the ship, and could not be found—I went after him, and found him at Islington—he was brought out of the theatre to me by his uncle—I asked him how he could do what he had done—he said he knew nothing about the money—I gave him in charge to the officer—he was dressed differently to what he was before—he had my boots on his feet—my cap was found in a bag which was in his aunt's possession—he was a good boy.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18471122-name-1339" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18471122-name-1339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
